# seeded-repo/ is a REAL git repository, generated by seeded-repo.build.sh.
# It is never checked in: a nested .git dir confuses the outer repo — verified
# empirically, `git add -A` stages it as an "embedded git repository" gitlink
# (mode 160000) with a loud warning, and a plain clone of the outer repo would
# then silently produce an empty seeded-repo/ (no .git, no files), since a
# gitlink records a commit hash, not content. This entry keeps an accidental
# `git add -A` from ever re-triggering that. See seeded-repo.build.sh and
# README.md in this directory for how to (re)build it.
seeded-repo/
